{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3259c519-4392-484d-abd8-275520fdefb0","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you need to make one change in your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n\n<!-- After — just delete the line, or: -->\n<UseVSTest>false</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nMSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is sufficient.\n\n### Key differences to be aware of:\n\n- **Running tests:** Use `dotnet test` as usual, but the underlying runner changes.\n- **CLI options** change (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--filter` still works but some advanced VSTest options differ).\n- **`runsettings`** files are still supported, but some VSTest-specific adapters/extensions may not carry over.\n- If you use `dotnet test`, add `--` before platform-specific options (e.g., `dotnet test -- --minimum-expected-tests 1`).\n\nNo additional NuGet packages are needed — the SDK handles the dependency wiring.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9dab2c91-5d87-470c-b8f4-2d0b6bf1922e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a configuration/knowledge question. Let me check if there's relevant documentation in the repository that might help.","outputTokens":359,"requestId":"0C06:2DCDB0:21BC91:27A8B6:69F00565"},"id":"fdb6c21e-891a-4f56-bb90-c794263e933e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:55:11.189Z","parentId":"29c5c1e5-4ed0-4571-9551-7927047e3d00"}
